<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="581" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,617,1002]" box="[151,1135,617,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,369,617,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Species examined:</emphasis>
female holotype (NHMUK 13454796); male (NHMUK 13454780).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,617,1002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,905,653,678]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
Description (Brunner von 
<bibRefCitation box="[521,726,653,678]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref5758" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1888) Monographie der Stenopelmatiden und Gryllacriden. Uerhandlungen der Kaiserlich- Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 38, 247 - 394, pls. 5 - 9." type="journal article">Wattenwyl, 1888</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[740,892,653,678]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref6195" refString="Karny, H. H. (1937) Orthoptera Fam. Gryllacrididae, Subfamiliae Omnes. Genera Insectorum, 206, 1 - 317." type="journal article">Karny, 1937</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Size small, wingless (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1256,653,678]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). With striking, dark brown to black colour patterns (
<figureCitation box="[570,660,689,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Head noticeably powerfully built (
<figureCitation box="[1071,1158,689,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Frons rough (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1422,689,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Fastigium of vertex wider than the first antennal segments. Tegmen and wing completely absent. Legs not overly long, always under 
<quantity box="[376,461,762,786]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
. Posterior femur with 5–6 internal and 3–4 outer ventral spines. Anterior and middle tibiae posteriorly more or less flattened dorsally, with four to six ventral movable spurs on each side. Abdomen of male with ninth tergite produced or hood-like (
<figureCitation box="[696,787,833,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
), with shallow median depression near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Male subgenital plate with clearly developed styli (
<figureCitation box="[866,954,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Female ovipositor not excessively long, under 
<quantity box="[221,304,906,930]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
; at the upper edge not serrated, apex acuminate or obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[960,1044,905,930]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1520,1542]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus basalis (Walker, 1869): head and pronotum in dorso-lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); face in anterior view (C); male abdominal apex in lateral (D) and ventral (E) views; female subgenital plate in ventral view (F); and female abdominal apex in lateral view (G). Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 2 mm (C–G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441897/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
